1
00:00:03,040 --> 00:00:05,360
Honey, maybe we should stop,
grab some bourekas, drinks, something?

2
00:00:05,440 --> 00:00:07,520
No, Dad said we don’t need to.
-Not appropriate.

3
00:00:07,600 --> 00:00:10,040
Not appropriate at all.
-No, Grandma Chava passed away.

4
00:00:10,120 --> 00:00:12,280
So there won't be anything inappropriate anymore, that's what I meant.

5
00:00:13,800 --> 00:00:15,240
Where do you go after you die?

6
00:00:16,280 --> 00:00:17,160
Probably

7
00:00:20,760 --> 00:00:23,040
After you die, you go to heaven.

8
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:25,760
Or, in Grandma Chava's case, hell.
-Shai.

9
00:00:26,440 --> 00:00:27,720
I don’t want to go to hell.

10
00:00:28,280 --> 00:00:30,880
You're not going to hell, honey,
we're going to Grandma Riki,

11
00:00:31,360 --> 00:00:33,640
which is a branch of hell, not the real place.

12
00:00:34,600 --> 00:00:38,600
But the kids' channel is the real place,
so Tal Musari is in hell?

13
00:00:38,680 --> 00:00:40,360
If there is a God, then yes.

14
00:00:46,160 --> 00:00:48,560
Look at me, look at me and...

15
00:00:57,240 --> 00:01:01,120
Come on, Riki, did you manage to sleep a bit?
-Where...

16
00:01:01,280 --> 00:01:04,519
I didn’t close my eyes, Pinchas snored like a horse.

17
00:01:04,840 --> 00:01:08,520
Pinchas, you need to take care of this.
-Okay.

18
00:01:08,640 --> 00:01:12,320
I told him to take care of it,
but it’s like talking to a wall.

19
00:01:12,440 --> 00:01:13,400
Okay.

20
00:01:13,480 --> 00:01:17,760
Pinchas, you really need to handle this.
-Maybe he doesn’t hear well either.

21
00:01:17,840 --> 00:01:19,760
I hear, I hear.

22
00:01:19,920 --> 00:01:22,520
I told him to go check his hearing,

23
00:01:22,600 --> 00:01:27,760
but it’s like talking to the chandelier.
-Okay, I’ll go, I’ll go.

24
00:01:27,920 --> 00:01:30,760
He’ll go when I grow hair here.

25
00:01:31,040 --> 00:01:35,560
Oh, you know I had hair here.
I removed it with laser.

26
00:01:35,640 --> 00:01:38,840
It’s unbelievable what you can remove today
with laser.

27
00:01:39,040 --> 00:01:40,480
Really?
-Hey there.

28
00:01:40,960 --> 00:01:42,560
What happened?
-Adam.

29
00:01:43,720 --> 00:01:45,720
I was scared it was a stranger,

30
00:01:46,760 --> 00:01:49,080
I don’t have the energy to host anymore,

31
00:01:50,040 --> 00:01:54,240
I hope people will have mercy
and not come to comfort us after Shabbat.

32
00:01:54,520 --> 00:01:56,200
You’re right, a little consideration.

33
00:01:57,160 --> 00:01:58,160
Do you want a cup of coffee?

34
00:01:59,120 --> 00:02:00,640
Thanks.
-Great.

35
00:02:01,160 --> 00:02:05,960
Adam, come to the kitchen,
make a cup of coffee for Mom and Aunt Shlomit.

36
00:02:06,520 --> 00:02:10,759
Pinchas, thanks, that’s very kind of you.
-No problem.

37
00:02:10,880 --> 00:02:13,920
Adam, did you leave the door open?
-Oh, right.

38
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:18,680
Ben, let it be over already.
-Shlomit, you put on too much makeup,

39
00:02:18,760 --> 00:02:20,840
it’s not respectful, it’s still a mourning period.

40
00:02:20,920 --> 00:02:25,280
You need to decide, it’s either heavy makeup
or stubble from four in the afternoon.

41
00:02:25,880 --> 00:02:28,680
You’ll still remove it with wax.

42
00:02:28,760 --> 00:02:31,000
Ben, at least you’ll meet Mom there.

43
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:36,560
That’s not nice. It’s funny, but it’s not nice.

44
00:02:41,440 --> 00:02:42,880
Oh, how sad.

45
00:02:43,560 --> 00:02:46,720
What coffee does Aunt Shlomit drink?
-Forget the coffee for now.

46
00:02:46,800 --> 00:02:49,280
What do you mean "forget the coffee,"
you said we’re making coffee, right?

47
00:02:49,840 --> 00:02:50,960
I want coffee too, do you want coffee?

48
00:02:51,040 --> 00:02:52,480
Can’t you see I’m in distress?

49
00:02:53,440 --> 00:02:56,160
I just got here, I didn’t have time.
-Adam, don’t annoy me, okay?

50
00:02:57,600 --> 00:02:59,800
I’m making you decaf.
-Forget the coffee.

51
00:03:00,280 --> 00:03:01,920
Don’t you understand my life is over?

52
00:03:03,840 --> 00:03:04,800
In what sense?

53
00:03:04,920 --> 00:03:08,320
In the sense that from the moment your uncle became an aunt

54
00:03:08,640 --> 00:03:10,840
he also became more of a mom than Mom.

55
00:03:13,120 --> 00:03:15,320
Dad, I still haven’t had coffee,
I need a bit more.

56
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:17,960
He enjoys making my life miserable.

57
00:03:18,440 --> 00:03:19,480
Just like Mom.
-Times two.

58
00:03:19,560 --> 00:03:22,640
I get it.
-She’s compensating for the years she was a man

59
00:03:22,840 --> 00:03:24,960
and he’s killing me.

60
00:03:25,880 --> 00:03:26,720
I understand.

61
00:03:27,600 --> 00:03:29,760
I get it, it’s been a tough week for you.

62
00:03:31,240 --> 00:03:33,360
So you know what I'm gonna do for you?
-What?

63
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:34,760
Hot chocolate.

64
00:03:39,080 --> 00:03:40,120
What time is it?

65
00:03:40,920 --> 00:03:42,320
Maybe they really won’t come.

66
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:45,880
I can’t talk anymore, I need some peace.

67
00:03:46,120 --> 00:03:49,640
All the time, "Why did Mom die?" She died,

68
00:03:49,760 --> 00:03:51,680
she was old and she died,

69
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:56,400
cause of death: life. What do people expect to hear?

70
00:03:56,960 --> 00:04:00,160
That it was a skydiving accident.
-Riki

71
00:04:02,360 --> 00:04:03,280
Sorry.

72
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:06,280
I was so scared.
-Sorry, sorry.

73
00:04:06,360 --> 00:04:08,800
You almost gave me a heart attack.
-Sorry.

74
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:13,760
Welcome.
-Hello, may you know no more sorrow, Riki.

75
00:04:13,840 --> 00:04:15,080
Silvan-

76
00:04:15,840 --> 00:04:18,160
My condolences.
-Rachel. And...

77
00:04:18,240 --> 00:04:23,400
-I’m sorry.
-And you brought your big little one with you.

78
00:04:24,120 --> 00:04:26,720
Meirav.
-Meirav, yes, Meirav,

79
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:29,560
Meirav, the chances I won’t forget anymore.

80
00:04:29,640 --> 00:04:30,640
Have a good week.

81
00:04:30,760 --> 00:04:32,440
Have a good week.
-Pinchas, Pinchas.

82
00:04:32,680 --> 00:04:35,480
I’m sorry for your loss.
-Silvan, Rachel, how lovely,

83
00:04:35,600 --> 00:04:37,000
Come closer, what a dish!

84
00:04:37,120 --> 00:04:38,760
K'
Y'
Ra
Roli' Abu

85
00:04:39,080 --> 00:04:42,240
What’s in the pot? Rachel, you didn’t have to.

86
00:04:42,320 --> 00:04:43,480
You should have.

87
00:04:43,560 --> 00:04:47,400
Maybe I’ll go put the pot in the kitchen?
-Yeah, go ahead, go ahead.

88
00:04:47,480 --> 00:04:50,600
Why "go ahead, go ahead"? We cleaned this week,
she’s got a pot in her hand.

89
00:04:50,720 --> 00:04:51,560
Come in, come in.
-Come on,

90
00:04:51,640 --> 00:04:53,360
Sit down, sit down.
-Sit down.

91
00:04:53,440 --> 00:04:56,560
Excuse me, are you sitting on armchairs?
-Yeah, what should we sit on?

92
00:04:57,120 --> 00:04:59,720
We do things differently here, we sit on the floor.

93
00:05:01,040 --> 00:05:02,960
Pinchas.
-Excuse me.

94
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:07,400
These are Shai's parents and this is...

95
00:05:09,200 --> 00:05:12,760
I’m Shlomit, nice to meet you, Rebecca's sister.

96
00:05:12,840 --> 00:05:14,640
Nice to meet you, nice to meet you,

97
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:17,800
May you know no sorrow, Shlomit.
-Thank you.

98
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:21,440
Tell me, do you smoke?
-Why, do you have something?

99
00:05:21,520 --> 00:05:23,480
Rachel, Rachel,

100
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:27,480
What’s in the pot you brought?

101
00:05:29,320 --> 00:05:32,200
Something small I brought for you to eat, curry.

102
00:05:32,680 --> 00:05:35,320
Thanks, I’ve never had that before.

103
00:05:35,880 --> 00:05:38,440
What’s curry?
-Meatballs in sauce.

104
00:05:40,240 --> 00:05:42,640
Meatballs?
Do you know what it’s called or
-How?

105
00:05:42,960 --> 00:05:44,080
Meatballs in sauce.

106
00:05:44,160 --> 00:05:45,120
That’s what I made.

107
00:05:47,480 --> 00:05:48,720
May you know no more sorrow, Adam.

108
00:05:52,040 --> 00:05:54,280
Thanks.
-Can I put the pot here?

109
00:05:54,360 --> 00:05:55,640
What did you bring?

110
00:05:55,720 --> 00:05:56,880
It’s meatballs in sauce.

111
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:58,840
Here.

112
00:06:00,440 --> 00:06:03,000
Sounds delicious, I’ve been living on bourekas for a week.

113
00:06:04,400 --> 00:06:07,760
Oh, a man like you needs meat.
-I love meat.

114
00:06:08,360 --> 00:06:09,440
There’s meat, and a lot of it.

115
00:06:11,040 --> 00:06:13,960
In the pot, I mean.
-Of course.

116
00:06:14,040 --> 00:06:16,800
I have insides.
-Of course you do.

117
00:06:17,360 --> 00:06:19,840
This is a new approach I’m trying, what do you think?

118
00:06:24,960 --> 00:06:26,320
May you know no more sorrow? No.

119
00:06:28,760 --> 00:06:30,480
We usually bring meat dishes during shiva.

120
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:36,160
Riki, should we tell them?

121
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:39,760
Shlomo, you’re killing me! Me too.

122
00:06:39,840 --> 00:06:41,360
Tell me, Shlomit, how come...

123
00:06:42,080 --> 00:06:45,720
We’ve never met?
-My husband and I live in Vienna.

124
00:06:46,760 --> 00:06:49,160
And where's your husband?
-He was here,

125
00:06:49,960 --> 00:06:53,320
He was at the funeral, just on Friday
he had to go back.

126
00:06:53,400 --> 00:06:57,440
Business, you know.
-Yeah, sure, I know, yeah.

127
00:06:58,200 --> 00:07:01,600
Are you here alone with them?
-Yeah.

128
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:04,360
Bless you.

129
00:07:04,840 --> 00:07:06,480
May you know no more sorrow.
-May you know no more sorrow.

130
00:07:07,040 --> 00:07:09,760
I guess we’re still in shock, but thank you.

131
00:07:11,320 --> 00:07:13,000
I’m going to get you some chairs.

132
00:07:13,080 --> 00:07:14,120
What did she die from?

133
00:07:14,520 --> 00:07:16,360
Ski accident.
-Riding.

134
00:07:16,920 --> 00:07:17,880
She died in her sleep.

135
00:07:17,960 --> 00:07:19,640
Holy.
-Thank you.

136
00:07:20,240 --> 00:07:21,920
I think she meant your mom.

137
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:24,000
Oh, she wasn’t holy.

138
00:07:24,760 --> 00:07:27,080
I have no idea who these people are.

139
00:07:28,360 --> 00:07:30,920
That’s how it is during shiva, people come by.

140
00:07:32,640 --> 00:07:33,760
What are you girls doing?

141
00:07:34,320 --> 00:07:36,760
My sweethearts, no running or shouting today, okay?

142
00:07:37,280 --> 00:07:38,360
Grandma is very sad.

143
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,760
So go to the balcony and I’ll call you.

144
00:07:41,120 --> 00:07:42,040
Quietly.

145
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:45,520
Honey.
-I’m exhausted.

146
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:48,920
Honey, we’ll be moving in twenty minutes max.

147
00:07:50,040 --> 00:07:51,280
Hello.
-Hey.

148
00:07:51,360 --> 00:07:53,240
Hi.
-How’s it going?

149
00:07:53,400 --> 00:07:55,520
Your family is here.
-Hey.

150
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:57,440
What’s this, Mom, I didn’t know you were coming today.

151
00:07:57,720 --> 00:08:00,280
We didn’t want to burden them at the start of shiva.

152
00:08:00,560 --> 00:08:03,800
Oh, yeah, you’re right,
at the beginning of shiva there’s still some sadness.

153
00:08:03,880 --> 00:08:05,840
Is Meirav here too?
-In the kitchen.

154
00:08:07,200 --> 00:08:08,920
Hi, Shlomit.
-Hi, sweetheart.

155
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:13,840
Honey, show me where the bathroom is.
-Sure, come on.

156
00:08:14,280 --> 00:08:19,040
What... how’s it going, Silvan?
-Good, everything’s fine.

157
00:08:20,040 --> 00:08:23,880
Just sitting and chatting with Shlomit, so nice,

158
00:08:23,960 --> 00:08:26,760
I just met her.
-How lovely.

159
00:08:28,480 --> 00:08:30,000
What’s this, why didn’t you tell me you were coming?

160
00:08:30,280 --> 00:08:31,840
What’s this, everyone’s coming.
-Everyone?

161
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:34,000
They’re bringing Alin, Orna, and Moshe.

162
00:08:34,080 --> 00:08:35,440
Why?
-They need to...

163
00:08:35,520 --> 00:08:37,640
Because they feel bad they didn’t make it to the funeral.

164
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:40,480
Tell me, why didn’t Shai say anything?
-Mom, come on,

165
00:08:40,559 --> 00:08:42,919
it’s some grandma he didn’t get along with, right?

166
00:08:43,039 --> 00:08:43,960
Still, it’s weird.

167
00:08:44,039 --> 00:08:47,200
Tell me, who’s that woman Dad is talking to?

168
00:08:48,280 --> 00:08:50,720
Aunt Shlomo.
-Explain.

169
00:08:51,280 --> 00:08:52,400
That’s...

170
00:08:52,840 --> 00:08:57,440
That’s Riki’s brother who recently decided to become her sister.

171
00:08:58,360 --> 00:08:59,440
14

172
00:08:59,640 --> 00:09:02,240
You’re telling me that...
-Yeah, totally.

173
00:09:03,120 --> 00:09:05,200
Totally totally?
-I don’t know, maybe.

174
00:09:08,280 --> 00:09:10,040
Mom, enough, quiet.

175
00:09:10,480 --> 00:09:12,960
Is that Riki’s brother?
-Yeah.

176
00:09:13,640 --> 00:09:14,560
Crazy, right?

177
00:09:15,840 --> 00:09:16,880
Mom.

178
00:09:17,360 --> 00:09:19,080
Mom, get a grip.

179
00:09:22,760 --> 00:09:26,520
Don’t tell Dad, it’s not nice.
-No, it’s not nice.

180
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:29,960
Mom, it’s shiva.
-Yeah.

181
00:09:30,720 --> 00:09:31,720
Herzl's dead.

182
00:09:32,760 --> 00:09:35,200
Yeah, Riki
-Yeah, Itamar.

183
00:09:35,680 --> 00:09:36,920
Itamar.
-Itamar.

184
00:09:37,560 --> 00:09:38,640
Hey.
-Where are you?

185
00:09:38,880 --> 00:09:40,360
Hi.
-Hey.

186
00:09:40,440 --> 00:09:41,640
Hi, wow.

187
00:09:42,280 --> 00:09:45,880
Who are those people that came before us?
-Distant relatives.

188
00:09:46,040 --> 00:09:46,880
What?

189
00:09:47,360 --> 00:09:50,080
Distant relatives, relatives from hell.

190
00:09:50,760 --> 00:09:52,320
Hey, what's up?
-Hey.

191
00:09:52,440 --> 00:09:54,080
Michal, do you remember my mom?
-Hey.

192
00:09:54,160 --> 00:09:55,360
Hi, how are you?

193
00:09:55,520 --> 00:09:57,160
What's up?
-All good.

194
00:09:57,480 --> 00:09:59,440
Grandma Chava passed away, you know, Chaim.

195
00:09:59,520 --> 00:10:01,040
Sit down, babe, come here for a sec.

196
00:10:03,600 --> 00:10:06,120
May you know no more sorrow.
-Right, yeah.

197
00:10:06,680 --> 00:10:09,000
So I don’t get why all this sadness is here.

198
00:10:09,320 --> 00:10:11,720
Excuse me for a sec. Babe, come with me, please.

199
00:10:13,400 --> 00:10:14,600
You know, Shlomit,

200
00:10:15,160 --> 00:10:20,240
in our mourning period
we don’t even send regards.

201
00:10:20,320 --> 00:10:23,640
What, he hasn’t found out yet?
-He doesn’t know anything.

202
00:10:27,360 --> 00:10:28,560
Tell me, why didn’t you tell me they were coming?

203
00:10:28,680 --> 00:10:30,840
I would’ve warned my parents.
-No, I didn’t know they were coming either.

204
00:10:30,920 --> 00:10:32,440
So, when are they leaving?
-What do you mean leaving?

205
00:10:32,520 --> 00:10:33,440
They’re going.

206
00:10:33,520 --> 00:10:35,360
No, first there’s a prayer.
-What prayer?

207
00:10:35,920 --> 00:10:38,080
A prayer, I don’t think my dad will go
before ten people show up.

208
00:10:38,160 --> 00:10:39,840
What ten?
-For the minyan.

209
00:10:39,920 --> 00:10:42,120
What minyan?
-Tell me, what’s wrong with you? What, are you a goy?

210
00:10:43,280 --> 00:10:47,360
I’ve been here twice this week, babe.
-Babe, brush your teeth and be quiet.

211
00:10:47,440 --> 00:10:48,400
Lips.

212
00:10:48,480 --> 00:10:50,320
What lips?
-No..

213
00:10:51,360 --> 00:10:53,560
Okay, we were here, can we go now?

214
00:10:53,640 --> 00:10:56,720
No, absolutely not, you’re staying here like a good kid from Givatayim.

215
00:10:56,800 --> 00:10:58,000
Jerusalem.

216
00:10:58,080 --> 00:11:00,440
What’s up with you today?
-I don’t like death, okay?

217
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:02,080
I want to go home.

218
00:11:02,520 --> 00:11:05,120
All this talk about death is killing me.
-No, I’m dying.

219
00:11:07,160 --> 00:11:09,880
May you know no more sorrow.
-So nice you came.

220
00:11:09,960 --> 00:11:11,240
Tbhm.
-Tbhmivan.

221
00:11:11,320 --> 00:11:12,560
Tbhmivan.
-Tbhmivan.

222
00:11:13,120 --> 00:11:14,560
This is Moshe.
-Right.

223
00:11:14,640 --> 00:11:15,640
You remember, right?

224
00:11:15,760 --> 00:11:18,240
This is Orna, she’s Shai’s sister,

225
00:11:18,480 --> 00:11:21,480
and Mavi and Alon, Shabi’s brother, you remember.
-Yeah.

226
00:11:21,560 --> 00:11:22,560
Tbhmivan.

227
00:11:22,680 --> 00:11:25,360
They grew up well with you, no evil eye.

228
00:11:25,440 --> 00:11:26,400
Ben Porat Yosef.
-Ben Porat Yosef.

229
00:11:26,560 --> 00:11:27,760
Come on, let’s put this in the kitchen.

230
00:11:29,240 --> 00:11:30,800
Pinchas, come here for a sec, just a moment.

231
00:11:34,800 --> 00:11:36,120
Itamar.

232
00:11:37,040 --> 00:11:39,240
May you know no more sorrow.
-Sure, sure.

233
00:11:39,320 --> 00:11:40,640
Ah, Moshe, what’s up?

234
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:43,080
What? Dying, huh?

235
00:11:43,240 --> 00:11:44,440
Yeah, soon at your place...

236
00:11:45,240 --> 00:11:47,840
Sorry, I apologize, a bit confused, dazed

237
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:49,720
and mostly don’t want to be here.

238
00:11:49,800 --> 00:11:50,640
You’re telling me.

239
00:11:50,920 --> 00:11:54,120
Shlomit, I’d like you to meet my family.

240
00:11:58,160 --> 00:11:59,000
Pinchas.
-What?

241
00:11:59,080 --> 00:12:01,200
What are they doing here?
-Who knows?

242
00:12:01,280 --> 00:12:05,440
The whole clan is here.
-They came to offer condolences.

243
00:12:05,520 --> 00:12:08,760
What's the point? You can't even mourn.

244
00:12:08,840 --> 00:12:12,000
Riki, they'll be here for... 20 minutes and then they'll leave.

245
00:12:13,080 --> 00:12:15,000
I'm telling you, Pinchas,

246
00:12:15,120 --> 00:12:19,440
His mom is watching us from above! She's cracking up.

247
00:12:20,040 --> 00:12:22,840
I'm telling you, it's hilarious.

248
00:12:27,400 --> 00:12:28,440
Say,

249
00:12:29,760 --> 00:12:33,040
Riki's sister.
-Yeah, she's transgender.

250
00:12:34,080 --> 00:12:36,560
You don't need to shout that,
his makeup is loud enough.

251
00:12:40,040 --> 00:12:41,440
Can we go now?
-No.

252
00:12:42,640 --> 00:12:43,680
And now?
-Itamar's giving a eulogy,

253
00:12:43,760 --> 00:12:45,760
Respect your grandma's memory.

254
00:12:45,840 --> 00:12:47,640
I don't want to, okay? I don't want to.

255
00:12:48,680 --> 00:12:51,000
I was at the funeral, I was here for the shiva for a few days,

256
00:12:51,960 --> 00:12:56,840
It's Saturday night now, I just want to sit
at home quietly and cry, for crying out loud.

257
00:12:57,880 --> 00:13:01,720
I want to remember my grandma in peace
in front of my TV.

258
00:13:01,880 --> 00:13:05,840
It's my right as an Israeli man to sit at home
on my couch and fart in peace.

259
00:13:05,920 --> 00:13:07,840
When was the last time you farted in peace?

260
00:13:08,600 --> 00:13:10,600
Just now.
-No way, I'm dying.

261
00:13:14,600 --> 00:13:16,880
Look, look, how nice.

262
00:13:17,560 --> 00:13:19,240
Now I need another one.

263
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:21,960
Are you waiting for someone?
-Yeah.

264
00:13:22,040 --> 00:13:23,320
For which guy?

265
00:13:24,280 --> 00:13:28,160
There are nine guys here, I need ten.

266
00:13:29,120 --> 00:13:30,920
You don't think twice?

267
00:13:31,360 --> 00:13:32,880
You're a real man.

268
00:13:37,720 --> 00:13:40,080
Ugh, but we never go anywhere.

269
00:13:40,160 --> 00:13:41,840
Because I'm telling you the kids are too grown up now

270
00:13:41,960 --> 00:13:43,120
and they don't care about this nonsense.

271
00:13:43,200 --> 00:13:44,880
I don't care about the kids, I was talking about me,

272
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:46,360
do you know how long it's been since I went to the safari?

273
00:13:47,120 --> 00:13:48,640
Go to the living room, there's a safari there.

274
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:51,360
We're going back to the living room and you can entertain yourself,

275
00:13:51,440 --> 00:13:52,560
be nice.

276
00:13:52,840 --> 00:13:54,520
Next Saturday we're going to the safari.

277
00:13:58,920 --> 00:14:02,160
Wow, I haven't been to the safari in weeks.

278
00:14:02,640 --> 00:14:04,360
Leave me out of the safari, just let me get home.

279
00:14:05,280 --> 00:14:07,160
We can pass by there on the way home.

280
00:14:07,480 --> 00:14:09,560
I read there was a giraffe birth there,

281
00:14:09,720 --> 00:14:11,080
it would be interesting to see a baby giraffe.

282
00:14:11,320 --> 00:14:13,440
I've always been curious to see it at eye level.

283
00:14:13,520 --> 00:14:16,360
Moshe, can you chill with the safari?
There's no safari, the safari is closed,

284
00:14:16,440 --> 00:14:17,880
the animals are on strike.
-What a shame.

285
00:14:17,960 --> 00:14:19,640
Focus on how we can get out of here the fastest.

286
00:14:21,360 --> 00:14:24,320
What, by running? Won't that look like something happened?

287
00:14:24,400 --> 00:14:26,600
Moshe, don't you get that we’re not leaving here

288
00:14:26,680 --> 00:14:29,320
until my dad organizes a minyan?
-Okay, okay.

289
00:14:33,520 --> 00:14:35,280
I wonder how much they pay for property tax here.

290
00:14:40,520 --> 00:14:41,720
Guys, have you eaten anything?

291
00:14:41,880 --> 00:14:43,320
Do you want to eat something?

292
00:14:43,560 --> 00:14:46,240
The food you brought is really tasty, honestly.

293
00:14:47,120 --> 00:14:51,440
Riki, do you want me to make you a plate?
-No, Rachel, I'd rather be alone

294
00:14:51,520 --> 00:14:54,440
and eat quietly after everyone leaves.

295
00:14:54,800 --> 00:14:58,800
Well, that could take hours.
-What hours? No way it’ll take hours!

296
00:14:59,360 --> 00:15:00,320
We need to pray, right?

297
00:15:02,720 --> 00:15:07,360
Mama, what did you do to me?
-Riki, it'll be fine.

298
00:15:10,040 --> 00:15:12,120
The potato salad is delicious, something else.

299
00:15:12,920 --> 00:15:15,280
Come on, Manny, when are we going home?

300
00:15:15,720 --> 00:15:18,400
I'm tired of playing waitress,
the kids are probably driving Mom crazy too.

301
00:15:18,880 --> 00:15:21,000
We can't leave until my dad
organizes a minyan and prays.

302
00:15:21,440 --> 00:15:23,400
What's the point of that?
-Are you crazy?

303
00:15:23,480 --> 00:15:24,320
What do you mean, what's the point?

304
00:15:24,400 --> 00:15:27,040
If they don't say Kaddish,
the soul of the deceased won't reach heaven, right?

305
00:15:27,120 --> 00:15:28,640
Sure, there's no chance she'll get there

306
00:15:29,080 --> 00:15:30,240
with all the saints in the world.

307
00:15:30,720 --> 00:15:31,720
Come on, that's not nice.

308
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:33,280
What, don't you have any good memories of her?

309
00:15:34,920 --> 00:15:36,000
I don't know?

310
00:15:37,320 --> 00:15:40,080
I remember we used to go to Grandma Chava's on Shabbat,

311
00:15:40,920 --> 00:15:44,280
and she had this really nice carpet
that you couldn't step on

312
00:15:45,400 --> 00:15:47,840
and couch covers you couldn't sit on

313
00:15:48,720 --> 00:15:51,320
in front of a TV that you couldn't turn on.

314
00:15:53,600 --> 00:15:56,200
That's how we were! Going to Grandma Chava's on Shabbat,
Shabbat at Grandma Savia's.

315
00:15:57,080 --> 00:16:01,080
I used to spend Shabbat at Grandma Yafa's,
Shabbat at Grandma Buba's.

316
00:16:01,160 --> 00:16:05,200
We spent Shabbat at Mazlika's and Shabbat at Shoshana's.

317
00:16:05,880 --> 00:16:07,280
I loved Grandpa Menachem.

318
00:16:09,520 --> 00:16:11,640
And then, one day, we stopped visiting the parents.

319
00:16:12,840 --> 00:16:14,120
It's so sad,

320
00:16:15,400 --> 00:16:17,560
suddenly one day they come to you for Friday night.

321
00:16:18,120 --> 00:16:20,640
Just like we stopped going to Grandma Mazal.

322
00:16:21,880 --> 00:16:23,960
I can't believe this is happening to me.
-What?

323
00:16:26,080 --> 00:16:27,680
That I'm at Grandma Chava's shiva,

324
00:16:29,240 --> 00:16:30,400
I really miss her.

325
00:16:32,680 --> 00:16:36,760
Hey, until Kaddish is said
can we jump to the safari in the meantime?

326
00:16:37,720 --> 00:16:38,880
It's 20 minutes from here.

327
00:16:38,960 --> 00:16:41,320
What safari are you talking about?
-Orna, drop it.

328
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:42,840
Moshe.
-What?

329
00:16:42,920 --> 00:16:44,200
Did you forget?
-What?

330
00:16:44,280 --> 00:16:46,280
The safari is closed, the animals are on strike.

331
00:16:46,760 --> 00:16:47,600
Sit.

332
00:16:49,840 --> 00:16:50,920
Come here for a sec.

333
00:16:59,080 --> 00:17:03,120
Sit down, my sweet,
I'm so glad your parents came

334
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:06,680
!your whole family, really a lovely bunch of people,

335
00:17:06,760 --> 00:17:10,880
and I'm so grateful they came to us.
-But?

336
00:17:11,839 --> 00:17:14,839
But I need your help.
What do I need to do to get them to leave?

337
00:17:15,800 --> 00:17:18,520
I'm tired, sit down.
-No, no, you're right, you're right, Riki,

338
00:17:18,599 --> 00:17:20,160
really, I understand you
and I also really want to help you,

339
00:17:20,240 --> 00:17:23,000
but my dad just wants to pray and needs a minyan.

340
00:17:23,560 --> 00:17:26,160
Minyan? How many is a minyan today?

341
00:17:27,160 --> 00:17:30,720
A minyan.
-Yeah, but you know, I didn't study in yeshiva

342
00:17:30,800 --> 00:17:33,000
!and my mom passed away this week, so how many is that, sweetie?

343
00:17:33,560 --> 00:17:35,120
Ten, that's ten men.

344
00:17:35,200 --> 00:17:36,960
How many do we have here?
-Nine.

345
00:17:37,520 --> 00:17:38,760
Can't we round that up?

346
00:17:40,520 --> 00:17:41,400
No.

347
00:17:41,480 --> 00:17:44,800
Sali, we can't skip on...
-No, we can't skip that.

348
00:17:45,760 --> 00:17:48,600
Someone needs to say Kaddish for their mom, who passed away,

349
00:17:49,440 --> 00:17:53,520
and if you're bored, you can go sit
next to Riki's sister, Shlomit,

350
00:17:53,600 --> 00:17:56,800
a really, really nice woman, very nice.

351
00:17:56,920 --> 00:17:57,760
Sali.
-What?

352
00:17:57,840 --> 00:17:59,320
There's something you don't know.

353
00:17:59,400 --> 00:18:02,640
Not now, not now, I'm asking you,
not now.

354
00:18:04,720 --> 00:18:06,480
Just so you know, your family is not normal.

355
00:18:07,160 --> 00:18:09,240
What do you want? My mom's mom passed away.

356
00:18:09,800 --> 00:18:11,560
Do you think I'm basing my stuff on the shiva?

357
00:18:11,880 --> 00:18:13,560
I'm talking to you about weeks of observations.

358
00:18:13,640 --> 00:18:15,600
Okay, sit down, babe, but good for you,

359
00:18:15,760 --> 00:18:17,520
your family isn't exactly normal either.

360
00:18:19,080 --> 00:18:20,640
Why is your dad insisting on praying now?

361
00:18:20,720 --> 00:18:23,880
What do you want, honey? It's fine with him.
-But it's not fine with us,

362
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:26,240
So maybe he'll respect his traditions?
-So what do you want,

363
00:18:26,360 --> 00:18:27,560
him to make schnitzel and mashed potatoes?

364
00:18:27,680 --> 00:18:29,040
Because those are the only things that are sacred to you.

365
00:18:29,120 --> 00:18:31,320
Right, schnitzel is sacred.
-Okay.

366
00:18:31,520 --> 00:18:33,440
Your meziluf isn't sacred?
-Yeah, the meziluf is,

367
00:18:33,520 --> 00:18:34,880
but there are other things.

368
00:18:38,600 --> 00:18:39,760
What, honey, what's going to happen?

369
00:18:41,600 --> 00:18:43,880
There's nothing to do, that's family for you,

370
00:18:45,120 --> 00:18:47,880
a collection of people with minor

371
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:48,880
or major mental issues.

372
00:18:50,600 --> 00:18:55,240
And meziluf, schnitzel, and love, that's it.

373
00:18:55,760 --> 00:18:56,960
Family, that's what we've got.

374
00:18:59,800 --> 00:19:02,520
Please, all the men in the room, raise your hands.

375
00:19:02,720 --> 00:19:04,160
Come on, I want to count.

376
00:19:04,840 --> 00:19:06,160
There are only nine, Mom.

377
00:19:06,720 --> 00:19:07,920
So we're just missing one.

378
00:19:08,480 --> 00:19:11,560
Go get a neighbor, Itamar.
-I tried, I knocked on all the doors,

379
00:19:11,640 --> 00:19:12,480
no one answered me.

380
00:19:12,560 --> 00:19:15,760
The Zigelmbims... I saw their light on.
When I knocked, they turned it off.

381
00:19:15,840 --> 00:19:19,480
I'll deal with them at the next homeowners' meeting.

382
00:19:19,640 --> 00:19:24,200
Okay, Shai, please go to the balcony, find
me a guy and bring him up.

383
00:19:24,680 --> 00:19:27,040
Maybe I should go down and try to hunt for guys.

384
00:19:27,120 --> 00:19:28,240
Maybe that's not a good idea.

385
00:19:28,960 --> 00:19:31,800
I can talk to someone from my friends
on Facebook, maybe someone nearby.

386
00:19:31,880 --> 00:19:34,160
Honey, you know
they're not really your friends, right?

387
00:19:34,240 --> 00:19:38,480
Why not? I've actually met quite a few
of my Facebook friends

388
00:19:38,600 --> 00:19:39,840
in person.

389
00:19:41,320 --> 00:19:44,280
Shai, sweetheart, do me a favor,
there's a Bukharian synagogue downstairs,

390
00:19:44,760 --> 00:19:45,680
you know where it is?

391
00:19:45,760 --> 00:19:47,480
Bring me a Bukharian, a nice one.
-What?

392
00:19:47,560 --> 00:19:51,680
No, no, no, no need,
not Bukharian, not Persian,

393
00:19:54,200 --> 00:19:55,600
not Austro-Hungarian.

394
00:19:56,360 --> 00:19:57,680
Shlomit, come here for a second.

395
00:20:05,280 --> 00:20:08,480
Sali, can I talk to you now?
-Yeah, about what?

396
00:20:10,120 --> 00:20:12,800
You miscounted, there are ten.

397
00:20:14,120 --> 00:20:16,680
I miscounted? What, can't I see well?
-No.

398
00:20:20,640 --> 00:20:23,400
You'll do it, for me.

399
00:20:25,920 --> 00:20:26,800
He what?

400
00:20:27,560 --> 00:20:29,320
Shlomo.
-Shlomo?

401
00:20:29,400 --> 00:20:33,640
It happened in the last two years.
-Why didn't you tell me?

402
00:20:33,720 --> 00:20:35,560
Because we couldn't disconnect you from him.

403
00:20:36,120 --> 00:20:39,720
Here’s Shlomo, there's a minyan.

404
00:20:40,280 --> 00:20:42,960
Shlomo?
-He has everything he needs.

405
00:20:44,520 --> 00:20:48,680
Silvan, can we say Kaddish already, for heaven's sake?
-Yeah, sure.

406
00:20:48,920 --> 00:20:50,320
Thank God.

407
00:20:51,280 --> 00:20:52,240
We need to say Havdalah first.

408
00:20:54,680 --> 00:20:58,160
I hope they left enough room in my mom's
grave

409
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:01,120
so she can turn over easily.

410
00:21:05,280 --> 00:21:06,280
That's it.

411
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:08,240
Yeah.

412
00:21:08,800 --> 00:21:11,000
We're going on vacation.
-Break.

413
00:21:11,600 --> 00:21:14,480
Next week there will be no schnitzels, no meziluf.

414
00:21:14,560 --> 00:21:17,200
Yeah, no Shleikler, no Shleimler.

415
00:21:17,280 --> 00:21:19,640
Big joy.
-Weird.

416
00:21:22,120 --> 00:21:23,960
Okay, put on a CD, play something.

417
00:21:27,960 --> 00:21:29,800
"Who loves Shabbat

418
00:21:29,960 --> 00:21:32,840
Mom! Dad

419
00:21:33,200 --> 00:21:35,200
Who loves Shabbat

420
00:21:35,280 --> 00:21:38,120
Grandma! Grandpa

421
00:21:38,440 --> 00:21:40,920
I love Shabbat.

422
00:21:41,080 --> 00:21:44,160
Me, you! You!

423
00:21:44,240 --> 00:21:48,280
Almost the whole world.

424
00:21:48,840 --> 00:21:53,720
So why not every Shabbat?

425
00:21:54,280 --> 00:21:58,680
Why not every Shabbat?

426
00:21:59,240 --> 00:22:04,240
Every Shabbat.

427
00:22:04,840 --> 00:22:07,000
How nice, you're making sounds, babe.
-Thanks.

428
00:22:10,240 --> 00:22:12,680
Tamari...
-Babe.

429
00:22:13,320 --> 00:22:14,840
Itamar.
-Hey there.

430
00:22:14,920 --> 00:22:16,960
Hey, come here.
-What?

431
00:22:19,480 --> 00:22:21,800
Orna and Alin! Moshe and...

432
00:22:23,200 --> 00:22:24,640
Manny.
-Everyone?

433
00:22:25,800 --> 00:22:27,600
I forgot the whole family.

434
00:22:27,680 --> 00:22:30,400
What, maybe we should stop somewhere
and grab some bourekas, drinks, something?

435
00:22:34,000 --> 00:22:36,200
What prayer?
-I don't think my dad...

436
00:22:37,920 --> 00:22:39,720
I don't like death, I don't like death.

437
00:22:40,360 --> 00:22:41,240
Sweetie.

438
00:22:42,200 --> 00:22:44,040
Enough, enough, I'm stopping...

439
00:22:46,840 --> 00:22:48,280
Moshe...

440
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:52,560
Shai, go down to MDA,

441
00:22:52,680 --> 00:22:54,880
to find me a guy, bring him up.

442
00:22:54,960 --> 00:22:55,960
Why MDA?

